    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe cursorline is embedded in the Window grid, which causes problems when scrolling in an UI like Neovide. This can be seen here, with a video https://github.com/neovide/neovide/issues/2818\r\n\r\n \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should be possible to use a UI protocol, so that we can deal with the cursorline ourselves, and do our own animations, totally decoupled from the grid scrolling itself.",
